32
00:03:04.601 --> 00:03:06.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No need to apologize!

33
00:03:06.436 --> 00:03:09.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're the only one I know
who's in the same boat as me!

34
00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:11.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have to help each other!

35
00:03:11.983 --> 00:03:15.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you've already helped me before.

36
00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:17.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, no shit.

37
00:03:18.031 --> 00:03:19.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I didn't ask for any of this!

38
00:03:19.699 --> 00:03:21.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That wasn't me.

39
00:03:23.202 --> 00:03:24.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

40
00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:26.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see.

41
00:03:26.748 --> 00:03:29.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you should just off that guy already.

42
00:03:29.834 --> 00:03:33.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not that easy, okay?

43
00:03:33.129 --> 00:03:36.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, do you have any leads
on who's behind all this?

44
00:03:37.383 --> 00:03:39.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, kind of.

45
00:03:39.093 --> 00:03:41.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Assuming the enemy
is not an organized entity,

46
00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:42.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
